{
  "slug": "rate-limiting-is-a-security-control",
  "title": "Rate limiting is a security control",
  "category": "security",
  "kicker": "Abuse prevention",
  "hook": "A system that accepts unlimited attempts is not being generous. It is volunteering for abuse.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-19",
  "tags": [
    "rate-limits",
    "abuse"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Attackers love cheap loops",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Login guesses, coupon brute force, scraping, OTP spam, and expensive search endpoints all get worse when the attacker can repeat them for free.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "edge · blocked burst",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "POST /login from 203.0.113.10 count=61/min",
              "c": "err"
            },
            {
              "t": "decision: challenge",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "next: block if failures continue",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "trust boundary",
          "nodes": [
            "input",
            "authn",
            "authz",
            "secrets",
            "deps",
            "egress"
          ],
          "caption": "Security gets real when the trust boundaries light up. Poke it and see what has to hold.",
          "action": "poke the boundary",
          "idle": "controls quiet",
          "running": "attack path lighting up...",
          "done": "6 security edges need review"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Limit by behavior, not just IP",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">IP limits help, but attackers rotate. Combine user, device, account, route, cost, and failure signals where it matters.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "abuse-limits.yml",
          "code": "login_failures:\n  key: account_id\n  limit: 5\n  window: 10m\n  action: step_up_challenge",
          "caption": "The best action is not always block; sometimes it is challenge."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Avoid punishing normal users",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A good abuse control makes attackers expensive while giving legitimate users a recovery path.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "security control lab",
          "caption": "Flip the switches and watch the story turn into a tiny operating model.",
          "toggles": [
            {
              "label": "object authz",
              "off": "route check only",
              "on": "resource access checked",
              "weight": 28
            },
            {
              "label": "rate limits",
              "off": "attackers get free loops",
              "on": "abuse has a cost",
              "weight": 24
            },
            {
              "label": "secret hygiene",
              "off": "tokens can leak into logs",
              "on": "values are redacted and rotated",
              "weight": 24
            },
            {
              "label": "threat model",
              "off": "risks discovered after build",
              "on": "boundaries reviewed early",
